committed
credit lines totaling $51.7 billion had been extended to us by 59 banks at
year-end 2009. availability of these lines is shared between ge and gecs with
$9.0 billion and $51.7 billion available to ge and gecs, respectively. the gecs
lines include $36.8 billion of revolving credit agreements under which we can
borrow funds for periods exceeding one year. additionally, $14.4 billion are
364-day lines that contain a term-out feature that allows ge or gecs to extend
the borrowings for one year from the date of expiration of the lending
agreement. we pay banks for credit facilities, but amounts were insignificant in
each of the past three years.
