when
stock options are exercised and restricted stock vests, the difference between
the assumed tax benefit and the actual tax benefit must be recognized in our
financial statements. in circumstances in which the actual tax benefit is lower
than the estimated tax benefit, that difference is recorded in equity, to the
extent there are sufficient accumulated excess tax benefits. at december 31,
2009, our accumulated excess tax benefits are sufficient to absorb any future
differences between actual and estimated tax benefits for all of our outstanding
option and restricted stock grants.
